cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on overfitting in deep learning, specifically in the context of class imbalance in image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes modifications to loss functions and regularizers, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of adversarial training and mixup also suggests a possible connection to the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as text classification, which could place it in the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
